@startuml django-keycloak-flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title Django + Keycloak OIDC Authentication Flow

actor User as user
participant "Browser" as browser
participant "Django App\n:8000" as django
database "Django DB\n(PostgreSQL)" as django_db
participant "Keycloak\n:8080" as keycloak
database "Keycloak DB\n(PostgreSQL)" as keycloak_db

== Startup ==
note over django, keycloak
  ./start.sh starts two Compose stacks on a shared Docker network:
  - compose/keycloak.yml  -> keycloak + keycloak-db
  - compose/django.yml    -> django + django-db
end note

== 1. User requests protected resource ==
user -> browser : Open /api/profile/
browser -> django : GET /api/profile/
django --> browser : 302 Redirect to /oidc/authenticate/
browser -> django : GET /oidc/authenticate/
django --> browser : 302 Redirect to Keycloak /auth\n(client_id=django-app, redirect_uri=callback)

== 2. Keycloak login ==
browser -> keycloak : Authorization request
keycloak -> keycloak_db : Validate realm + client config
keycloak --> browser : Login page
user -> browser : Enter username/password
browser -> keycloak : POST credentials
keycloak -> keycloak_db : Authenticate user + load roles
keycloak --> browser : 302 Redirect to Django callback\n?code=AUTHORIZATION_CODE

== 3. Token exchange + user sync ==
browser -> django : GET /oidc/callback/?code=...
django -> keycloak : POST /token\n(code, client_secret)
keycloak --> django : id_token + access_token
django -> django : KeycloakOIDCAuthenticationBackend\nmaps ID token + access token claims
note right of django
  Userinfo is skipped: tokens are issued
  for localhost:PORT but Django calls
  Keycloak internally at keycloak:8080
end note
django -> django_db : CREATE or UPDATE user\n(is_staff from admin role)
django -> django : Store tokens + roles in session
django --> browser : 302 Redirect to /api/profile/

== 4. Authenticated API response ==
browser -> django : GET /api/profile/ (session cookie)
django -> django_db : Load user from session
django --> browser : 200 JSON profile

== 5. Logout ==
user -> browser : Click logout
browser -> django : GET /oidc/logout/
django -> django : Clear Django session
django --> browser : Redirect to Keycloak logout
browser -> keycloak : End SSO session
keycloak --> browser : Redirect to Django home

@enduml
